  <li><a href="https://www.eea.europa.eu/themes/air/health-impacts-of-air-pollution">Air pollution: how it affects our health - European Environment Agency (website)</a></li>
</ul>

<h1 id="smoking">Smoking</h1>
<p>Smoking can have many negative health effects, for smokers and those around smokers, for example in the form of impaired lung function, increased risk of cancer, and accelerated aging. David Sinclair and Matthew LaPlante write on pages 71-72 of their book <em>Lifespan</em>:</p>

<blockquote>
  <p>“We know that smoking accelerates the aging clock and makes you more likely to die than a nonsmoker – 15 years earlier, on average.”</p>
</blockquote>

<h2 id="recommendations-10">Recommendations</h2>
<ul>
  <li>Do not smoke</li>
</ul>

